724466f-a.text:
677 West End Avenue, west side, between 92nd and 93rd Streets, a private house built in the mid 1890's. The adjoining house, No. 675, will give way to a modern apartment building in 1923. See
view of the whole block in that year.
About 1912.
724466f-a.folder: West End Avenue & 92nd Street (West), Manhattan, NY

724467f-a.text:
West End Avenue, west side, from 93rd to 92nd Streets, showing new 675 West End Avenue, a 15-story apartment building rising on the site of old 667-75, five-stony private houses. No. 677, adjoining it on the north, is pictured in more detail in a 1912 photograph.
1923.
724467f-a.folder: West End Avenue & 92nd Street (West), Manhattan, NY

724465f-a.text:
West End Avenue, east side, from 92nd to 93rd Streets, showing 660 to 678 West End Avenue. They will be replaced before 1930 by two apartment buildings, the 22-story Windemere in the southern half of the block, and the 15-story building in the northern half of the block.
June 1925.
